bioghist.head: Historical Note

p.emph: Founded in 1908 from a law program initiated at Transylvania University in 1799, the University of Kentucky J. David Rosenberg College of Law was one of the nation's first state law schools. In 1913 the College established the nation's first law school trial practice program, and its Kentucky Law Journal is the tenth-oldest student-run law review in the nation. The J. David Rosenberg College of Law has been approved by the American Bar Association since 1925 and was elected to Order of the Coif, the most prestigious national legal honorary society, in 1931.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The University of Kentucky. College of Law Composite Class Photographs (dated 1897-2020; bulk 1910-2020; 8.68 cubic feet; 6 flat boxes, 12 oversize folders; 108 Gigabytes, 387 files) comprise composite photographs of individual images of each member of each graduating class of the College of Law, 1910-2016. Composites 2017 and onward are born-digital. Composites for graduating years 1912-1917 and 1944-1945 are not present. There is also a digitized image of the composite photograph of the University of Louisville Department of Law graduates and faculty, 1897.
